Your goal in this game is to dock the boats without sinking it, if you hit other boats or parts of the dock the game can be over and you need to start again. So sail carefully! So don't hit anything because you don't want any damage to your precious boat.

H-aKUEwQbWI.title: How to make flannel baby blankets
H-aKUEwQbWI.description:
EDIT: Thanks to people being unable to read annotations or something I'm disabling comments due to all the folks who leave stupid remarks about the cats. I'm tired of deleting them. Hope you like the video, if not, go eat a hairball.

I'd just like to emphasize that I DID NOT MAKE THIS VIDEO. MY AUNT DID. I AM JUST POSTING IT FOR HER (WITH HER PERMISSION). 

That being said, in an effort to slow the tide of humorless comments, a few things should be noted:

This video has been getting a lot of comments from people concerned about the presence of allergens from the cats that might be harmful to the babies for which the blankets were made. These people should be relieved to know that 1) they do not need cats present in order to make the blankets themselves, and 2) the blankets were laundered before being given away. And probably laundered AGAIN by the parents before being brought into proximity with their baby. So you may stop filling the comments with your worries and (if I must say) rather unrealistic requests that the video be remade, sans cats.

Cats are everywhere. And they know where you live. Be kind to them.

Or else.

----

My aunt Rachel made this video three years ago and wanted me to post it on my account because she is too lazy to get her own YouTube account. She has trouble with the thought of remembering yet another username and password.

So here you have her video of how to make flannel baby blankets using two pieces of flannel. One piece should be 1.5 yards and the other should be 1 yard. This is for 44/45" fabric (standard size). It takes about an hour to make one start to finish, and an hour and a half to make two. You don't have to wash the fabric ahead of time, in fact it's better not to, and then just wash the blanket once it is done.

Warning: contains cats.
